                <head>No. 352.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Fish</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Riotte</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1872-02-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">February</hi> 22, 1872</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 68.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>. Referring to your dispatch No. 97, of the 21st
                    ultimo, on the subject of the exploration of the Nicaraguan Isthmus, with a view
                    to the construction of an interoceanic canal, I have to inform you that an
                    expedition for that purpose has been ordered by this Government, and that a
                    vessel may be expected in Nicaragua in a few weeks, to begin the survey. I take
                    this occasion to acknowledge the receipt of your dispatch No. 96, of the 11th
                    ultimo.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>HAMILTON FISH.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
